<br />
Which would only somewhat make sense if it was one person and all they were looking at was the Wizard list. The reason this idea comes up a lot is because people forget there aren't really 10 issues here, there are actually 180 issues of which 10 are Wizard issues. All of the lists get consolidated and then the actual issues are sent to the people responsible for the areas that the items fall under. In a nutshell, making it nine issues wouldn't get anything actually done faster or get those nine issues looked at more, it would just mean we only had nine issues.<br />
<br />
Anyways, this is off topic, if you want to discuss it more, make a new thread about it.</div>
